namespace Gnosis

-- 1. The Gnostic Mass/Energy Scale
-- We map the integer Gnostic numbers onto bounded particle states.
-- Barbelo (1) represents the fundamental unconfined excitation (the Photon/Spark).
-- Proton (3) represents the fundamental tri-confined state (Baryon/Quark triplet).
inductive GnosticParticle
| spark   -- Gnostic 1 (Photon analog)
| dyad    -- Gnostic 2 (The unknown Syzygy particle)
| triplet -- Gnostic 3 (Proton analog)


-- 2. The Topological Necessity of the Dyad Particle (The Syzygon)
-- If we treat the structural states as generated by the Gnostic Ladder (which strictly follows the Fibonacci sequence here: 1, 2, 3, 5...),
-- then the existence of 1 (Photon) and 3 (Proton) mathematically forces the existence of 2 (The Syzygon).
-- A system transitioning from a tri-confined state (3) to an unconfined state (1) MUST pass through a di-confined state (2) because the topological crossing invariant cannot jump by 2 without a Reidemeister phase.


-- 3. Proof of Existence: The Syzygon (The Anti-Parallel Pair)
-- When a Triplet (3) decays or interacts to produce a Spark (1), 
-- it absolutely must generate a topological state of crossing index 2.

end Gnosis